cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about improving NLP tasks using word embeddings. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a new approach to generating embeddings using a learned function. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with improving generalization in NLP tasks. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper uses subword RNNs to generate embeddings. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with improving performance on tagging tasks, which can be relevant to computer vision applications.
